'''Madeleine Dalphond-Guiral''' (born June 6, 1938) is a [[Canadian]] nurse, professor and politician.

Dalphond-Gurial was a [[registered nurse]] by training and later a professor of nursing. She was first elected to the [[House of Commons of Canada]] as a [[Bloc Québécois]] MP for the riding of [[Laval Centre]] in the [[Canadian federal election, 1993|1993 federal election]]. She served as [[Official Opposition]] Deputy [[parliamentary whip|Whip]] from 1994 to 1996, Chief BQ Whip from 1996 to 1997 and again as Deputy Whip until 2000. She also served in the BQ [[shadow cabinet]] as Citizenship and Immigration Critic from 2000 to 2004. She did not run in the [[Canadian federal election, 2004|2004 federal election]].

