{{about||the second year in history|AD 2|the Batman comic book|Batman: Year Two}}
'''Year Two''' is an educational [[year group]] in schools in many countries including [[England]], [[Wales]], [[Australia]] and [[New Zealand]]. It is usually the second year of compulsory education and incorporates students aged between six and eight.

==Australia==
In Australia, Year Two is usually the second year of compulsory education. Although there are slight variations between the states, most children in Year Two are aged between seven and eight.<ref name="aus">{{Cite web|url=http://www.mceetya.edu.au/verve/_resources/Volume_1_CSSA_Final_Report.pdf|title=Cost/Benefit Analysis Relating to the Implementation of a Common School Starting Age and Associated Nomenclature by 1 January 2010|accessdate=2009-01-10|publisher=Atelier Learning Solutions Pty Ltd|format=PDF}}</ref>

==New Zealand==
In New Zealand, Year Two is the second year of compulsory education. Children are aged six or seven in this year group.
<ref name="NZ">{{Cite web|url=http://www.teamup.co.nz/Child/SchoolEducation/SchoolBasics/SchoolYearsAndLevels.aspx|title=School years and levels|accessdate=2009-01-10|publisher=Ministry of Education|work=Team-up website}}</ref> Year Two pupils are usually educated in [[Primary school]]s or in [[Area school]]s.<ref name="NZ2">{{Cite web|url=http://www.teamup.co.nz/Child/SchoolEducation/SchoolBasics/TypesOfSchools.aspx|title=Types of schools|accessdate=2009-01-10|publisher=Ministry of Education|work=Team-up website}}</ref>

==United Kingdom==
===England===
In schools in [[England]] Year Two is the second year after [[Reception (school)|Reception]]. It is the second full year of compulsory education, with children being admitted who are aged 6 before 1 September in any given academic year. The equivalent form in the [[US]] is [[1st grade]]. <ref name="ncuk">{{Cite web|url=http://curriculum.qca.org.uk/key-stages-1-and-2/Values-aims-and-purposes/about-the-primary-curriculum/index.aspx|title=About the primary curriculum|accessdate=2009-01-10|publisher=Qualifications & Curriculum Authority|work=National Curriculum Website}}</ref>

Year Two is usually the third and final year in [[Infant school|infant]] or the third year of [[primary school]].

===Wales===
In schools in [[Wales]] Year Two is the second year after [[Reception (school)|Reception]]. It is currently the second full year of compulsory education, with children being admitted who are aged 6 before 1 September in any given academic year. It is currently part of [[Key Stage 1]], although from 2011 will form the final of four years in the [[Foundation phase]].<ref name="wales">{{Cite web|url=http://new.wales.gov.uk/topics/educationandskills/policy_strategy_and_planning/104009-wag/foundation_phase/?lang=en |title=What is the Foundation Phase? |accessdate=2009-01-10 |publisher=Welsh Assembly Government |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090720133754/http://new.wales.gov.uk/topics/educationandskills/policy_strategy_and_planning/104009-wag/foundation_phase/?lang=en |archivedate=20 July 2009 }}</ref>

===Northern Ireland and Scotland===

In [[Northern Ireland]] and [[Scotland]], the second year of [[compulsory education]] is called Primary Two, and pupils generally start at the age of 5.

